<item>
            <title>[LU-18244] add &apos;lfs mkdir -C -N&apos; overstriping support</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18244</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/35034&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/35034&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12273&quot; title=&quot;DNE3: Metadata overstriping&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12273&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12273&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lod: metadata overstriping&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; it is possible to create overstriped directories across MDTs using &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs mkdir -C &lt;em&gt;N&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, and with patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/54192&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/54192&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16938&quot; title=&quot;&amp;quot;lfs setstripe -C -1&amp;quot; stripes too widely, should be limited to OST_COUNT&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16938&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16938&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; utils: setstripe overstripe multiple OST count&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; it is possible to specify an overstripe factor for each OST for &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs setstripe -C -&lt;em&gt;N&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, it is not possible to specify &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs mkdir -C -&lt;em&gt;N&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to specify an overstripe factor for each MDT.  It would be good to fix this inconsistency.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
